  "texts": [
    "BMI was calculated by dividing self-reported weight (kg) by height squared (m 2); with reference to 25 kg/m 2, participants were categorized as being of normal weight or obese [19].",
    "Cold-heat pattern identification is a Korean medicine pattern identified for each person, based on their preference or sensitivity to cold or hot temperatures and the temperature of their hands and feet.",
    "In traditional East Asian medicine, this pattern is used to provide health management for patients [20].",
    "We used the cold-heat pattern identification questionnaire to analyze the cold and heat pattern scores, which consists of eight items for cold pattern and seven items for heat pattern [21].",
    "The cold and heat pattern scores were calculated sum of the items included in each pattern on a five-point response scale from 1 to 5, with higher scores indicating closer to being in a cold or heat pattern."
  ],
